1
00:00:13,232 --> 00:00:14,096
Gita!

2
00:00:17,403 --> 00:00:19,428
I want to talk to you
about something important.

3
00:00:20,406 --> 00:00:22,431
I cannot keep it in me anymore.

4
00:00:23,576 --> 00:00:24,941
Go on.

5
00:00:26,579 --> 00:00:29,104
I had recognized you at the
bookshop in Delhi.

6
00:00:30,182 --> 00:00:32,946
And I'd guessed that you had
come to take Kaveriamma away.

7
00:00:33,819 --> 00:00:36,652
You did not make a mistake
in the address of Charanpur.

8
00:00:37,590 --> 00:00:39,717
I had deliberately given you
the wrong directions.

9
00:00:42,261 --> 00:00:44,161
Why is that?

10
00:00:45,931 --> 00:00:47,228
Call me childish...

11
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:51,395
... but I did not want you
to reach Charanpur

12
00:00:52,271 --> 00:00:53,738
and to meet Kaveriamma.

13
00:00:55,274 --> 00:00:59,404
For all that you're doing for the
school, I'd like to thank you!

14
00:01:01,113 --> 00:01:03,411
But I cannot let you take
Kaveriamma away.

15
00:01:03,616 --> 00:01:04,480
Why?

16
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:06,474
You want her so that

17
00:01:07,286 --> 00:01:10,255
she can take care of your house
and do all the household chores.

18
00:01:10,456 --> 00:01:11,423
How dare you say that?

19
00:01:12,124 --> 00:01:13,751
How can you accuse me
of such a motive?

20
00:01:14,126 --> 00:01:15,923
I have travelled 12,000 miles
only out of concern for...

21
00:01:16,462 --> 00:01:17,929
... Kaveriamma's well being.

22
00:01:18,130 --> 00:01:19,757
If you were so concerned

23
00:01:20,132 --> 00:01:22,600
then where were you when she
was in an Old Age Home?

24
00:01:22,801 --> 00:01:25,065
It was I who traced her
and got her here.

25
00:01:25,471 --> 00:01:28,099
Maybe, that's because

26
00:01:28,374 --> 00:01:31,468
you needed someone to take
care of Chikku and your house.

27
00:01:36,148 --> 00:01:37,775
Why did you come back?

28
00:01:39,318 --> 00:01:41,115
Why did you have to come back?

29
00:01:43,322 --> 00:01:45,290
We were so happy.

30
00:01:46,825 --> 00:01:48,986
You have everything in life.

31
00:01:51,330 --> 00:01:55,289
But all we have is Kaveriamma.

32
00:01:57,169 --> 00:01:59,501
You are not the only one
with a right over her.

33
00:02:02,675 --> 00:02:07,135
I agree that she is
like a mother figure to you...

34
00:02:07,846 --> 00:02:09,473
... and you like a son to her.

35
00:02:11,850 --> 00:02:13,477
But she is a mother to me too.

36
00:02:16,855 --> 00:02:21,155
I don't want to
become an orphan again!

37
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,520
I understand Gita.

38
00:02:30,035 --> 00:02:32,663
I will not allow you to take
Kaveriamma away from me.

39
00:02:37,209 --> 00:02:39,609
Kaveriamma will come
with me to America.

40
00:02:42,881 --> 00:02:46,442
Whether you like it... or not!

41
00:03:09,408 --> 00:03:11,774
I'm in a dilemma Fatima.

42
00:03:12,077 --> 00:03:16,207
Mohan is asking me to go with him,
while Gita expects me to be here.

43
00:03:16,415 --> 00:03:17,541
I just don't know what to do.

44
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:21,880
Allah knows, when Mohan arrived
I was so happy for you.

45
00:03:22,087 --> 00:03:25,181
But I never thought things
would get into such a tangle.

46
00:03:25,424 --> 00:03:28,825
You'll have to disappoint
one or the other.

47
00:03:28,927 --> 00:03:34,593
I'm not clear whether I should go to
America with Mohan or not!

48
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:40,235
I don't understand why he
wants to take you there?

49
00:03:40,439 --> 00:03:44,808
To work there? Did you ask him?

50
00:03:45,611 --> 00:03:51,743
No Fatima. He respects me.
He'll take good care of me.

51
00:03:52,017 --> 00:03:54,952
Well, I hope you are right Kaveri.

52
00:03:55,287 --> 00:03:58,984
Otherwise who is to know what
tomorrow has in store?

53
00:04:02,127 --> 00:04:06,655
Kaveri, why don't you ask
Mohan to stay on over here?

54
00:04:07,065 --> 00:04:10,330
No, he won't agree.

55
00:04:10,636 --> 00:04:12,831
Remember one thing...

56
00:04:13,205 --> 00:04:17,107
... every piece of ice is inevitably
ordained to melt in its own water!

57
00:04:17,309 --> 00:04:20,176
Get him to understand
this perfectly well.

58
00:04:39,498 --> 00:04:40,760
We played a lot.

59
00:04:43,268 --> 00:04:44,735
Kaveriamma...

60
00:04:45,003 --> 00:04:47,870
... you can stop looking
for a groom for me!

61
00:04:48,173 --> 00:04:51,142
I have decided... not to get
married at this point!

62
00:04:51,343 --> 00:04:53,004
But why?

63
00:04:53,679 --> 00:04:59,879
Yes. I want to focus all my time on the
children and the school's progress.

64
00:05:00,686 --> 00:05:03,416
That's alright, but...

65
00:05:03,689 --> 00:05:06,852
Furthermore, I'm not yet prepared
for marriage!

66
00:05:14,032 --> 00:05:16,466
Well done!

67
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:20,930
This is a good move
to stall Kaveriamma from leaving.

68
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:26,439
But then, come to think of it
who will want to marry you anyway?

69
00:05:26,645 --> 00:05:29,614
Now, don't get me wrong!
I'm not saying you're not beautiful.

70
00:05:29,882 --> 00:05:35,184
But this attitude, tonnes of
ideals and principles...

71
00:05:35,387 --> 00:05:37,252
... who'll suffer all this?

72
00:05:37,890 --> 00:05:40,825
It's a good thing, you have
decided to opt out yourself.

73
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:46,964
But there is one crazy guy,
who might want to marry you.

74
00:06:00,345 --> 00:06:02,711
Yes Mohan, the precipitation
measurement list has been drawn up.

75
00:06:02,981 --> 00:06:05,848
You understand what I'm saying?
- Yes Vinod.

76
00:06:06,084 --> 00:06:10,384
We've tested the dual frequency radar,
the horizontal & vertical resolution's fine

77
00:06:10,589 --> 00:06:17,222
Yes, but the waveforms need to match
with the longitudinal parabolas.

78
00:06:17,429 --> 00:06:19,226
Of course, of course
they work in alignment.

79
00:06:19,598 --> 00:06:20,860
Nivaaranji... Nivaaranji...

80
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:23,393
Here speak to Steve.
- Hi Mohan.

81
00:06:23,602 --> 00:06:27,732
Steve, what about the
geometrical axis function?

82
00:06:28,273 --> 00:06:33,006
It's being calibrated. The baseline
parameter's been optimized.

83
00:06:33,445 --> 00:06:38,815
See, the sun-synch orbit needs to be in
alignment with the radiometers of TRMM.

84
00:06:39,451 --> 00:06:41,749
Ok, I'll make the remaining readings
and call you in a couple of days.

85
00:06:42,054 --> 00:06:43,316
Ok, thanks.

86
00:06:43,789 --> 00:06:47,316
Hey Mohan so how's everything else?

87
00:06:47,626 --> 00:06:49,651
Everything's fine. All is well.

88
00:06:49,962 --> 00:06:51,930
So, have you found yourself
a village belle?

89
00:06:52,297 --> 00:06:53,423
Actually, you can say yes.

90
00:06:53,532 --> 00:06:54,897
What?

91
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:57,658
You're kidding me right?
- No.

92
00:06:58,804 --> 00:07:00,795
What's her name?

93
00:07:01,139 --> 00:07:04,540
Her name is Gita.
Kaveriamma lives with her.

94
00:07:04,810 --> 00:07:06,471
I don't believe this!

95
00:07:06,812 --> 00:07:08,473
Except, she's no village belle...

96
00:07:08,814 --> 00:07:11,476
She studied in Delhi
and now she runs a school here.

97
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:13,948
Have you told her?

98
00:07:14,319 --> 00:07:15,616
Does she know?

99
00:07:15,988 --> 00:07:17,956
How can I tell her?
- What do you mean?

100
00:07:18,156 --> 00:07:19,555
I mean...

101
00:07:20,325 --> 00:07:25,627
I mean she's got a different set
of ideals et al. She's just different.

102
00:07:25,998 --> 00:07:28,398
Come on!
You can't make that mistake.

103
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:30,134
You have to tell her how you feel.

104
00:07:30,502 --> 00:07:32,129
All right... if you say so.

105
00:07:32,337 --> 00:07:34,464
Listen I'll catch up with you later,
gotta go now.

106
00:07:34,673 --> 00:07:38,336
Your two weeks are almost up!

107
00:07:39,011 --> 00:07:40,069
I know.

108
00:07:40,345 --> 00:07:41,471
I'll be back soon.

109
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:45,275
You should have been back already.
- But let me propose to her first.

110
00:07:45,684 --> 00:07:48,084
I'll be leaving soon,
catch up with you later, bye.

111
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,209
Bye.

112
00:07:51,356 --> 00:07:53,347
Gurnaamji, how much was that?

113
00:07:56,361 --> 00:07:59,194
32 minutes. Is it ok if I pay tomorrow?
- Yes.

114
00:07:59,531 --> 00:08:03,331
My apologies Mohanbabu!
The electricity is problematic here.

115
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:37,031
Why are you trying to
corrupt Chikku's mind?

116
00:08:37,235 --> 00:08:38,862
What are you talking about?

117
00:08:39,071 --> 00:08:42,529
Haven't you been talking to him and
his friends about going to America?

118
00:08:42,741 --> 00:08:44,208
No Gita, I was just explaining...

119
00:08:44,409 --> 00:08:48,709
Am I teaching these kids so that they can
go abroad and settle down like you?

120
00:08:48,914 --> 00:08:51,974
You NRI. Non-Returning Indian!

121
00:08:55,754 --> 00:08:57,278
Hand me the mug, please.

122
00:08:58,757 --> 00:09:01,726
You don't even know how to have a bath.
You should learn from Chikku.

123
00:09:01,927 --> 00:09:03,394
Gita, I think you need a vacation.

124
00:09:03,762 --> 00:09:06,026
Why don't you come back
with me for one?

125
00:09:08,266 --> 00:09:10,063
Gita, you are very mischievous.
Where's the bucket?

126
00:09:10,268 --> 00:09:11,735
Listen...
- No. You listen to me.

127
00:09:11,937 --> 00:09:15,737
What?
- I like you very much... Gitli!

128
00:09:16,108 --> 00:09:18,076
What?!
- It's true, Gitli!

129
00:09:18,443 --> 00:09:23,039
I liked the way you handled
that man in the bookshop.

130
00:09:23,381 --> 00:09:27,750
Don't try to sweet talk me.
Kaveriamma will stay here... with me!

131
00:09:27,953 --> 00:09:30,581
You're misunderstanding.
I really like you.

132
00:09:30,956 --> 00:09:34,084
Shut up! And don't you try
to corrupt the kids again, ok?

133
00:09:34,292 --> 00:09:37,557
I'm not corrupting anyone.
I'm only bathing.

134
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:44,396
More than the kids, you're the
one who needs an education!

135
00:09:49,307 --> 00:09:51,707
You can keep calling out to
YOUR Kaveriamma now.

136
00:10:06,158 --> 00:10:10,652
All right now, remove your notebooks.
The topic is General Knowledge.

137
00:10:10,996 --> 00:10:12,224
So who's going to tell me...

138
00:10:12,430 --> 00:10:16,730
... the names of five of the most
important rivers in the country?

139
00:10:18,603 --> 00:10:20,798
I'm sorry to be late teacher.

140
00:10:31,283 --> 00:10:33,080
Look ahead.

141
00:10:37,689 --> 00:10:39,884
Today I'm going to take your class!

142
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,725
First question...

143
00:10:44,029 --> 00:10:47,328
... name five main rivers in India?

144
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,164
You...

145
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:52,962
... tell me!

146
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,337
Let me think.

147
00:10:58,643 --> 00:11:02,602
Ganga, Jamuna, Narmada...

148
00:11:05,383 --> 00:11:07,010
... Bharati...

149
00:11:08,553 --> 00:11:09,679
... Panchgani...

150
00:11:09,888 --> 00:11:14,154
Bharati? Panchgani??
Are they rivers?

151
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:17,221
Vidya, you tell me.

152
00:11:17,562 --> 00:11:22,363
Ganga, Jamuna, Narmada...
Godavari and Brahmaputra.

153
00:11:26,671 --> 00:11:28,161
Excellent Vidya!

154
00:11:29,908 --> 00:11:31,239
Second question...

155
00:11:32,077 --> 00:11:36,980
... name the new state that has
been formed in North-West India?

156
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:42,318
I know this one.
It was a part of Uttar Pradesh, right?

157
00:11:46,758 --> 00:11:48,316
Yes Chikku. You tell us!

158
00:11:48,593 --> 00:11:50,060
It's Uttaranchal!
- Oh yes, Uttaranchal!!

159
00:11:50,262 --> 00:11:52,196
How could I have missed it?
I forgot!

160
00:11:53,098 --> 00:11:54,690
Well done, Chikku!

161
00:11:55,934 --> 00:11:57,595
Now the last question...

162
00:11:57,936 --> 00:12:01,463
... if our new student does
not know the answer...

163
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:04,841
... we'll have to demote him to
a lower class.

164
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:23,518
How many lion heads does
the Ashoka pillar have?

165
00:12:27,632 --> 00:12:29,065
This one is easy.

166
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:30,297
Three.

167
00:12:30,635 --> 00:12:33,570
Noooooo! It's got four!

168
00:12:36,141 --> 00:12:39,110
Excellent, children!
The lesson of the day is...

169
00:12:39,311 --> 00:12:41,279
... before gaining knowledge
about foreign lands,

170
00:12:41,579 --> 00:12:45,140
it is important that one should
know one's own country first.

171
00:12:50,655 --> 00:12:52,850
Don't forget to do your homework.

172
00:13:00,432 --> 00:13:03,868
The rivers Ganga and Jamuna have
their confluence point in Allahabad.

173
00:13:04,169 --> 00:13:05,932
The new state Uttaranchal...

174
00:13:06,171 --> 00:13:09,470
... is the 27th state of India
with Dehradun as its capital.

175
00:13:09,674 --> 00:13:12,472
This is the land where the
Mahabharata was written!

176
00:13:12,844 --> 00:13:15,039
The Ashoka pillar rests
in a circular abacus,

177
00:13:15,347 --> 00:13:18,475
which is girded by four animals.
The bull of the West...

178
00:13:18,783 --> 00:13:26,554
... the elephant of the East,
the horse of the South...

179
00:13:26,858 --> 00:13:28,758
... and lion by the North.

180
00:13:32,864 --> 00:13:38,996
Gita, the blackboard is clean.

181
00:13:46,378 --> 00:13:48,175
Gita... I am...

182
00:13:52,384 --> 00:13:53,612
Gita... !

183
00:13:57,889 --> 00:13:59,720
But all my answers were correct.

184
00:14:00,225 --> 00:14:04,025
This is Natthu, the potter and
this is Shankar...

185
00:14:04,229 --> 00:14:05,355
... he makes baskets.

186
00:14:05,563 --> 00:14:09,499
Both of them want us to admit
their children in school.

187
00:14:09,734 --> 00:14:12,362
What Mohanbabu said to us
the other day touched our hearts.

188
00:14:12,737 --> 00:14:16,730
We don't want our
children to suffer like us.

189
00:14:17,242 --> 00:14:19,369
On the morning of Dussehra
<i>(Indian festival)</i>

190
00:14:19,744 --> 00:14:22,372
you can come and enroll your
children in the school.

191
00:14:22,580 --> 00:14:24,275
Yes ok.

192
00:14:28,253 --> 00:14:30,380
The tides have begun to
change direction.

193
00:14:30,755 --> 00:14:32,154
Haven't they?

194
00:14:41,766 --> 00:14:43,324
I'm sorry.

195
00:14:54,279 --> 00:14:56,247
Mohan!- Yes?

196
00:14:57,615 --> 00:15:01,574
Mohan, I have some work for you.
- What work?

197
00:15:01,786 --> 00:15:03,913
There's a place called Kodi a
few miles from here.

198
00:15:04,289 --> 00:15:06,416
Gita has some family property there,

199
00:15:06,791 --> 00:15:09,259
which has been leased to a
farmer called Haridas.

200
00:15:09,627 --> 00:15:12,118
He has not paid his rent for
some months.

201
00:15:12,297 --> 00:15:14,060
I want you to go an
recover the money.

202
00:15:14,632 --> 00:15:15,758
Me?

203
00:15:16,634 --> 00:15:18,932
But why do you want me to go?
Can't you send someone else?

204
00:15:19,237 --> 00:15:22,331
If you go and ask
he just might pay up.

205
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:25,507
Oh! So you want me
to be a collector now!

206
00:15:25,810 --> 00:15:29,974
Ok, when should I leave?
I have to fuel up the caravan.

207
00:15:30,315 --> 00:15:32,283
You have to leave now.
- Now?

208
00:15:32,484 --> 00:15:35,942
Yes, and you can't take the caravan there.
- Then?

209
00:15:36,321 --> 00:15:38,448
You will have to take the train
for three hours to Narsinga...

210
00:15:38,656 --> 00:15:40,715
... then a boat journey across
the river to Maangaon...

211
00:15:41,059 --> 00:15:44,290
... and finally three hours by bus...
and you've reached Kodi!

212
00:15:44,496 --> 00:15:49,058
Sure, that's pretty closeby!
- You'll return by tomorrow evening.

213
00:15:49,334 --> 00:15:53,566
And Mela Ram will go with you.
He knows the way.

214
00:15:54,839 --> 00:15:57,205
Kaveriamma...
- Yes?

215
00:15:58,943 --> 00:16:03,380
My vacation is nearing it's end.
What have you decided?

216
00:16:04,949 --> 00:16:07,315
You finish this work first.

217
00:16:13,024 --> 00:16:14,889
Come on Collector saheb... !

218
00:16:18,863 --> 00:16:20,262
Why are you sending Mohan?

219
00:16:20,465 --> 00:16:23,161
I sent Haridas a message only
a few days ago.

220
00:16:24,202 --> 00:16:26,898
I know what I'm doing!

221
00:16:35,613 --> 00:16:38,173
Good morning sir.
- Good morning Melaram.

222
00:16:38,383 --> 00:16:41,784
I'm all set to take you on a
sightseeing trip of the village.

223
00:16:48,393 --> 00:16:49,553
Ok, I'll take your leave.

224
00:16:49,727 --> 00:16:52,560
Mohanbhaiyya, you'll
bring me a toy, won't you?

225
00:16:52,730 --> 00:16:56,131
Of course! Gimme five... yes!

226
00:17:06,244 --> 00:17:08,974
And what shall I bring for you?

227
00:17:09,414 --> 00:17:10,847
Nothing.

228
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:17,710
I know you don't want me to leave,
but I have to go for Kaveriamma.

229
00:17:18,423 --> 00:17:21,415
And listen, don't think
about me too much.

230
00:17:22,093 --> 00:17:23,856
Don't miss me too much.

231
00:17:24,429 --> 00:17:27,865
Now what makes you think
that I'll miss you?

232
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:29,866
The look in your eyes!

233
00:17:31,769 --> 00:17:33,634
They give your feelings away.

234
00:18:15,313 --> 00:18:17,941
O beloved, most beloved, surely

235
00:18:18,149 --> 00:18:21,209
I am infatuated with thee

236
00:18:21,486 --> 00:18:24,614
Thou hast endeared my heart

237
00:18:24,822 --> 00:18:28,280
O beloved...

238
00:18:31,162 --> 00:18:33,960
O beloved, most beloved, surely

239
00:18:34,332 --> 00:18:37,233
I am infatuated with thee

240
00:18:37,502 --> 00:18:40,630
Thou hast endeared my heart

241
00:18:40,838 --> 00:18:43,705
O beloved...

242
00:18:43,941 --> 00:18:46,967
My heart's bewildered

243
00:18:47,178 --> 00:18:50,147
My body with fire kindled

244
00:18:50,348 --> 00:18:53,317
It's monsoon of my dreams

245
00:18:53,518 --> 00:18:56,487
The courtyard of my eyes streams

246
00:18:56,854 --> 00:18:59,823
The pitcher of my heart is overflowing

247
00:19:00,024 --> 00:19:06,987
O beloved...

248
00:19:41,899 --> 00:19:47,769
O dear who hast drawn so near!
O dear who hast endeared my heart!

249
00:19:48,072 --> 00:19:50,870
How canst I recount

250
00:19:51,242 --> 00:19:55,338
What hath been thy bequest pray how?

251
00:19:56,247 --> 00:19:59,216
Somewhere art buds of
a throbbing heart

252
00:19:59,417 --> 00:20:02,386
Somewhere the dream-lanes

253
00:20:02,587 --> 00:20:05,556
Mirth that dwells in the heart,

254
00:20:05,757 --> 00:20:08,385
How shallst I articulate?

255
00:20:08,593 --> 00:20:11,562
Thou swayeth me so

256
00:20:11,763 --> 00:20:16,598
That oft times I am embarrassed

257
00:20:16,801 --> 00:20:23,138
It seems I have lost
my path

258
00:20:23,341 --> 00:20:29,337
Ever since I have seen the
haven of love

259
00:20:29,547 --> 00:20:32,380
Haven of love

260
00:20:32,784 --> 00:20:35,878
O beloved, most beloved,
surely

261
00:20:36,087 --> 00:20:38,988
I am infatuated with thee

262
00:20:39,223 --> 00:20:42,283
Thou hast endeared my heart

263
00:20:42,493 --> 00:20:45,690
O beloved...

264
00:21:21,666 --> 00:21:28,037
Now that thou hast met me
This world's transformed

265
00:21:28,239 --> 00:21:34,235
Methinks the flowers have begun
to beset my path

266
00:21:34,445 --> 00:21:39,940
And I fancy too
That this earth's renewed

267
00:21:40,151 --> 00:21:47,319
The sky too freshly spun
in our love

268
00:21:47,658 --> 00:21:50,593
Wanton breeze singeth some melody

269
00:21:50,795 --> 00:21:55,732
River too narrates some tale

270
00:21:55,933 --> 00:22:02,270
All's changed, my love
since my eyes courted thine

271
00:22:02,473 --> 00:22:08,571
I have lost presence of my mind,
gone is my treasured selfhood

272
00:22:08,779 --> 00:22:12,738
O beloved...

273
00:22:30,835 --> 00:22:32,803
Haridasji!

274
00:22:37,174 --> 00:22:38,198
Haridasji!

275
00:22:38,843 --> 00:22:39,867
Yes?

276
00:22:45,149 --> 00:22:47,845
I'm Mela Ram and this is
Mohan Bhargavaji.

277
00:22:48,185 --> 00:22:49,209
Tell me.

278
00:22:49,353 --> 00:22:53,722
Kaveriji and Gitaji have sent me.
It's about the land's rent.

279
00:22:56,027 --> 00:22:57,221
I understand.

280
00:22:57,862 --> 00:22:59,830
Come in.

281
00:23:07,038 --> 00:23:11,270
You have travelled a long way.
You must be tired. Please rest.

282
00:23:12,209 --> 00:23:14,143
Make some bread.

283
00:23:15,212 --> 00:23:16,839
Run along now.

284
00:23:18,049 --> 00:23:19,141
Please come in.

285
00:23:36,233 --> 00:23:38,599
You really shouldn't have bothered.

286
00:23:40,071 --> 00:23:43,768
How is that possible?
A guest is like God!

287
00:23:44,742 --> 00:23:48,007
We've served what we have;
you eat and then we'll talk.

288
00:23:48,579 --> 00:23:49,568
Ok.

289
00:24:03,761 --> 00:24:08,130
If I had the capacity to pay,
I would have come to Charanpur myself.

290
00:24:08,766 --> 00:24:12,600
Sir, I was a weaver before I
took up farming.

291
00:24:13,771 --> 00:24:16,239
Since the advent of machine
woven fabrics in the market,

292
00:24:16,941 --> 00:24:18,875
weaving had ceased to
be a lucrative business.

293
00:24:20,177 --> 00:24:24,773
So I became a farmer.
I took Gitaji's land on lease.

294
00:24:26,283 --> 00:24:32,222
I'd imagined, once the crops flourished
the children's life would improve.

295
00:24:34,291 --> 00:24:35,815
But it was not to be!

296
00:24:37,628 --> 00:24:38,652
Why?

297
00:24:39,964 --> 00:24:43,764
By taking up farming,
I had changed my profession.

298
00:24:45,136 --> 00:24:50,005
The village elders did not accept this
and looked upon me as an outcast.

299
00:24:51,976 --> 00:24:57,039
They felt a weaver should remain a weaver,
even if it meant, that he had to go hungry.

300
00:24:58,983 --> 00:25:04,250
I cried, pleaded...
but no one listened to me!

301
00:25:05,990 --> 00:25:10,051
Nobody offered a drop of
water to irrigate my land.

302
00:25:12,329 --> 00:25:13,853
Entire crop dried up...

303
00:25:15,166 --> 00:25:18,932
.... and whatever survived,
the villagers refused to buy.

304
00:25:20,671 --> 00:25:23,697
It is because of this, I've not
been able to pay Gitaji's rent.

305
00:25:25,843 --> 00:25:26,935
But this is wrong.

306
00:25:30,014 --> 00:25:34,041
It's unfair. It is an outrage!

307
00:25:34,518 --> 00:25:36,611
It is the way things work here.

308
00:25:38,689 --> 00:25:40,554
Not a morsel to
fill our stomach,

309
00:25:41,692 --> 00:25:45,890
no clothes to wear,
no roof above our heads,

310
00:25:46,864 --> 00:25:49,628
no education for children,
nor land!

311
00:25:50,868 --> 00:25:56,431
The thirst in my heart alone
knows the taste of my tears!

312
00:25:59,043 --> 00:26:00,237
Then what did you do?

313
00:26:00,711 --> 00:26:01,837
What could I do?

314
00:26:03,047 --> 00:26:06,778
I thought about migrating to the city,
hoping life would be better there.

315
00:26:08,552 --> 00:26:11,578
Those who had been there,
recounted the anguish in the cities.

316
00:26:13,057 --> 00:26:18,518
A labourer goes there to work,
and falls into the grip of contractors.

317
00:26:20,231 --> 00:26:25,760
He either returns hungry,
or never returns.

318
00:26:27,071 --> 00:26:30,837
And soon, the wife has to
sell the little land she has.

319
00:26:31,742 --> 00:26:33,266
No sir, no!

320
00:26:34,078 --> 00:26:37,946
I couldn't feed my
children in this life...

321
00:26:39,917 --> 00:26:41,612
... what is to happen after me?

322
00:26:42,753 --> 00:26:45,813
And about Gitaji's money,

323
00:26:47,091 --> 00:26:51,892
I have nothing to offer
except helplessness and shame.

324
00:26:53,597 --> 00:26:54,621
Nothing...

325
00:27:11,115 --> 00:27:14,915
Thank you for the food, Haridasji.

326
00:27:51,822 --> 00:27:53,187
Haridasji, I'll take your leave.

327
00:27:58,829 --> 00:28:02,697
Please don't mind. Here's
some money. Keep it.

328
00:28:03,167 --> 00:28:07,297
Mohanbabu, it's very kind of you
but I can't accept it.

329
00:28:07,671 --> 00:28:09,468
Please Haridasji, I want you to keep it.

330
00:28:09,673 --> 00:28:12,369
When you have it, you can
return it to me.

331
00:28:12,676 --> 00:28:16,442
But I don't know when I will
be able repay it.

332
00:28:18,849 --> 00:28:19,873
Don't worry about it.

333
00:28:22,186 --> 00:28:26,247
Here Chotu, this is for you.
Share it with your sisters.

334
00:28:29,193 --> 00:28:33,892
Please give Gitaji
and Kaveriji my respects.

335
00:30:04,621 --> 00:30:15,429
Water for sale... water for sale...
25 paise for a glass...

336
00:30:24,641 --> 00:30:29,010
25 paise for a glass of water...

337
00:30:29,980 --> 00:30:31,504
Saheb, please have a glass of water.

338
00:32:23,427 --> 00:32:24,894
Mohan you're back!

339
00:32:32,936 --> 00:32:34,494
How was your journey?

340
00:32:35,772 --> 00:32:38,036
Ok.
- Did you meet Haridas?

341
00:32:38,942 --> 00:32:41,809
Yes. But I could not get the money.

342
00:32:46,283 --> 00:32:50,811
His situation is pathetic.
He can't pay the rent!

343
00:32:51,121 --> 00:32:54,579
Instead, sir gave him money
from his own pocket, before leaving.

344
00:32:56,627 --> 00:32:58,822
I couldn't bear to see
Haridas' condition.

345
00:33:02,132 --> 00:33:04,464
I don't think you should expect
any rent from him.

346
00:33:07,137 --> 00:33:09,230
Mohanbhaiyya, did you get me my toy?

347
00:33:12,976 --> 00:33:14,534
I couldn't get anything.

348
00:33:18,482 --> 00:33:19,676
Come Chikku.

349
00:33:27,658 --> 00:33:30,627
Mohan this is the general
state of affairs.

350
00:33:32,162 --> 00:33:35,757
What is money when compared
with the value of human life?

351
00:33:37,167 --> 00:33:39,692
I'm glad you gave him money.

352
00:33:40,837 --> 00:33:45,536
Now don't get disheartened.
Rest a little.

353
00:34:00,090 --> 00:34:01,216
Kaveriamma...

354
00:34:02,859 --> 00:34:04,690
... how do I wrap this around?

355
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:12,725
Kaveriamma has left for school.
For the decorations.

356
00:34:13,203 --> 00:34:16,104
I don't know why she wants
me to wear this dhoti?

357
00:34:16,373 --> 00:34:18,068
What's wrong with my jeans anyway?

358
00:34:18,208 --> 00:34:21,177
It is the appropriate thing to
wear on Dussehra.

359
00:34:21,378 --> 00:34:22,709
If you wish I can tie it for you.

360
00:34:22,879 --> 00:34:25,347
How do you know?
Have you ever worn one?

361
00:34:25,549 --> 00:34:27,016
It's not a saree, ok!

362
00:34:27,384 --> 00:34:29,249
Ok then! Do it yourself.

363
00:34:29,386 --> 00:34:33,413
All right, all right.
Just do it quick.

364
00:34:33,890 --> 00:34:34,914
Come...

365
00:34:39,563 --> 00:34:40,587
Give...

366
00:34:42,733 --> 00:34:43,757
Hold it.

367
00:35:01,918 --> 00:35:03,317
What the...

368
00:35:41,792 --> 00:35:43,225
There, it's done.

369
00:35:46,797 --> 00:35:48,287
Sure, it's done...

370
00:35:48,799 --> 00:35:52,200
... but I hope it doesn't
unravel in a crowd! Or else...

371
00:35:52,402 --> 00:35:53,426
Shut up!

372
00:35:56,306 --> 00:35:59,764
Today is the auspicious day of Dussehra.
It was on this day that Lord Rama...

373
00:35:59,976 --> 00:36:05,107
had slain Ravana and marked the
triumph of good over evil!

374
00:36:05,315 --> 00:36:11,584
I am very happy that on this day
we initiate new students in the school.

375
00:36:23,333 --> 00:36:24,800
May the Goddess of Knowledge
be with you.

376
00:36:25,001 --> 00:36:26,263
It's Lajwa.

377
00:36:34,511 --> 00:36:37,207
This is our little granddaughter Kusum!

378
00:36:42,018 --> 00:36:43,883
Now, go and play.

379
00:36:48,692 --> 00:36:54,289
Mohanji, where are you off?
Why don't you spend some time with us?

380
00:36:56,032 --> 00:36:59,160
I'm impressed. How well you've
tied your dhoti Mohanbabu?

381
00:36:59,369 --> 00:37:01,166
How did you manage to learn so quickly?

382
00:37:01,371 --> 00:37:03,839
It's pretty easy. It was tied in seconds.

383
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:05,735
You're looking like a bridegroom.

384
00:37:08,445 --> 00:37:09,241
Thank you.

385
00:37:09,379 --> 00:37:13,475
So how long have you lived abroad?

386
00:37:13,717 --> 00:37:16,015
It's been almost twelve years now.

387
00:37:16,219 --> 00:37:19,086
You must have adapted yourself
completely to their way of living?

388
00:37:20,390 --> 00:37:25,851
We would also like to know a
thing or two about America.

389
00:37:26,396 --> 00:37:31,231
Well... America is a big country...

390
00:37:31,401 --> 00:37:35,360
We've heard that it's also very rich?

391
00:37:35,739 --> 00:37:39,004
Rich it is. But there are several
reasons for that.

392
00:37:39,242 --> 00:37:43,679
One among them is that their land
is rich in mineral resources...

393
00:37:43,914 --> 00:37:47,247
Even our land is rich, but in crops.

394
00:37:47,417 --> 00:37:50,011
Our strength... lies in our fields.

395
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:52,388
Do they have problems of rain?

396
00:37:52,589 --> 00:37:56,047
Are they affected by drought
and famine like us?

397
00:37:56,259 --> 00:37:58,056
And what about electricity?

398
00:38:01,765 --> 00:38:05,565
They've set up infrastructure to provide
all the basic amenities to the common man.

399
00:38:05,769 --> 00:38:11,833
Electricity, housing board, healthy
food and free education.

400
00:38:12,042 --> 00:38:19,414
We have one thing,
they don't have and will never have.

401
00:38:20,784 --> 00:38:21,808
What?

402
00:38:22,285 --> 00:38:24,583
Culture and tradition!

403
00:38:24,788 --> 00:38:25,948
Yes, agreed.

404
00:38:26,122 --> 00:38:31,924
And till we have that,
no one can destroy us.

405
00:38:32,295 --> 00:38:35,924
Ours is the greatest country in the world!

406
00:38:36,466 --> 00:38:37,262
Absolutely!

407
00:38:37,467 --> 00:38:42,666
Culture and tradition is our strength,
don't you agree?

408
00:38:46,643 --> 00:38:47,940
Munishwar...

409
00:38:49,145 --> 00:38:53,844
I don't think... Mohanbabu agrees!

410
00:38:53,984 --> 00:38:55,178
Do you Mohanji?

411
00:38:56,152 --> 00:38:57,346
You're right.

412
00:38:58,321 --> 00:39:01,347
I don't agree that ours is the greatest
country in the world!

413
00:39:05,829 --> 00:39:11,028
But I do believe that we have the
potential and strength to become great.

414
00:39:13,169 --> 00:39:18,106
Both these countries are economically,
sociologically and culturally apart.

415
00:39:18,842 --> 00:39:23,302
I shouldn't say this but since you have
broached this topic, let me say that...

416
00:39:24,180 --> 00:39:26,774
... whenever we suspect losing
in comparison...

417
00:39:27,183 --> 00:39:29,447
... we clutch on to our favourite refuge...

418
00:39:30,854 --> 00:39:31,843
... culture...

419
00:39:32,522 --> 00:39:33,853
... and tradition!

420
00:39:35,058 --> 00:39:37,083
America has progressed
on its own strengths.

421
00:39:37,193 --> 00:39:39,161
They have their own culture
and own tradition.

422
00:39:39,362 --> 00:39:42,490
It would be wrong to claim
that their culture

423
00:39:42,699 --> 00:39:45,896
their tradition and beliefs
are inferior and ours are laudable.

424
00:39:46,703 --> 00:39:47,897
It's wrong.

425
00:39:49,673 --> 00:39:51,766
But I have heard that

426
00:39:51,975 --> 00:39:57,641
there they discriminate against
members of ethnic races.

427
00:39:57,881 --> 00:40:01,339
Yes! There are clashes sometimes.
Aren't they everywhere?

428
00:40:01,551 --> 00:40:05,920
What is important to analyze is that
we make differences based on caste.

429
00:40:07,924 --> 00:40:15,626
You talk as if we have created the caste,
class, religion and the social system.

430
00:40:16,132 --> 00:40:20,125
This hierarchy of caste is ancient
as is culture and religion.

431
00:40:20,770 --> 00:40:23,204
And colour and creed.

432
00:40:23,406 --> 00:40:27,536
Remember, one's caste is
a thing that can never die!

433
00:40:27,744 --> 00:40:30,872
Just because a custom is ancient,
it does not have to be right.

434
00:40:32,248 --> 00:40:36,548
Why are you imposing your
views on us Mohanbabu?

435
00:40:37,520 --> 00:40:39,579
I am not imposing any views.

436
00:40:39,923 --> 00:40:44,223
I am only speaking of things I've
experienced while living here.

437
00:40:44,995 --> 00:40:47,555
And I've realized that we keep
fighting amongst ourselves...

438
00:40:47,664 --> 00:40:52,226
... when we must fight against illiteracy,
over-population and corruption.

439
00:40:52,502 --> 00:40:57,235
Every day, in our streets and homes,
each one of us keeps saying

440
00:40:57,574 --> 00:41:01,840
"The country has gone to dogs. The
country is on the path of destruction!"

441
00:41:02,345 --> 00:41:06,406
If we keep saying this, we will
one day actually land up there.

442
00:41:06,616 --> 00:41:08,345
You'll need to do
something to remedy this.

443
00:41:08,451 --> 00:41:09,748
You too!

444
00:41:09,953 --> 00:41:12,615
Not just the members of the Panchayat
but everyone in the village.

445
00:41:14,224 --> 00:41:17,387
You are blaming the members of the
Panchayat for your problems.

446
00:41:17,694 --> 00:41:22,757
But when you step into their shoes, you'll
do the same thing. This applies to me too!

447
00:41:23,666 --> 00:41:25,463
The dalits blame the brahmins...

448
00:41:25,602 --> 00:41:29,333
... and brahmins claim that their
piety is despoiled by the dalits.

449
00:41:29,973 --> 00:41:33,272
The blacksmith and potter blame
the moneylender.

450
00:41:34,277 --> 00:41:37,906
The land owners blame the peasants,
but they don't give them their rights.

451
00:41:38,815 --> 00:41:41,943
In what way are we great then?

452
00:41:42,619 --> 00:41:44,883
If we have problems in the village,
we point our finger at the State...

453
00:41:45,088 --> 00:41:49,855
... and the State at someone else.
We all are finding fault with each other!

454
00:41:50,293 --> 00:41:53,729
The fact is that we're all to be blamed.

455
00:41:54,330 --> 00:41:56,798
Because the problem... is us!

456
00:41:57,133 --> 00:41:59,226
Me... you...

457
00:42:00,303 --> 00:42:01,793
... all of us!

458
00:42:02,572 --> 00:42:06,440
Have you lost your head?
What are you saying?

459
00:42:07,143 --> 00:42:08,735
All I know is that...

460
00:42:09,779 --> 00:42:14,113
... a weaver who changed his
occupation by becoming a farmer...

461
00:42:15,351 --> 00:42:18,548
... cannot feed his family

462
00:42:20,557 --> 00:42:23,287
or give his children an education.

463
00:42:24,260 --> 00:42:27,627
He can only watch his kids
die of malnutrition.

464
00:43:14,144 --> 00:43:20,379
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

465
00:43:20,984 --> 00:43:27,389
O scion of Raghu race,
come to rescue me

466
00:43:28,391 --> 00:43:32,828
Come, O Raghu stalwart,
O lord, I beseech thee

467
00:43:33,029 --> 00:43:37,159
Adorable lord of my heart,
O my good Ram, appear

468
00:43:37,367 --> 00:43:41,997
I recite thy Name,
hear thou O Ram and come

469
00:43:42,205 --> 00:43:44,173
I recite thy Name,

470
00:43:44,374 --> 00:43:48,071
hear thou O Ram and come

471
00:43:48,278 --> 00:43:50,143
Proclaim glory of truth
by beat of drum,

472
00:43:50,580 --> 00:43:52,741
burn Lanka of sins

473
00:43:53,016 --> 00:43:57,749
At once come, rescue me and
heed loud proclamation mine

474
00:43:57,954 --> 00:44:04,291
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

475
00:44:04,794 --> 00:44:11,063
O scion of Raghu race,
come to rescue me

476
00:44:21,010 --> 00:44:24,946
Forget Ram, look!
It's Ravana who hast come

477
00:44:25,181 --> 00:44:29,515
His mighty shadow hath
spread over all quarters

478
00:44:29,852 --> 00:44:35,518
Why dost thou recite Name of Ram?
Why dost thou sing rosary of Ram?

479
00:44:35,825 --> 00:44:39,955
This Ram - Ram thou hast
begun by rote

480
00:44:40,163 --> 00:44:41,425
O Sita!

481
00:44:41,631 --> 00:44:45,658
what virtue didst thou
see in Ram to quote?

482
00:44:46,269 --> 00:44:50,171
Who can recount all His virtues?

483
00:44:50,406 --> 00:44:54,934
Lexicon too falleth short

484
00:44:55,445 --> 00:44:59,404
Who can reach the summits

485
00:44:59,649 --> 00:45:04,086
Where my adorable Ram sits

486
00:45:04,621 --> 00:45:08,990
Ram is most excellent in this world,
unswerving in virtue

487
00:45:09,192 --> 00:45:13,424
Most puissant yet
possessed of restraint

488
00:45:13,630 --> 00:45:17,828
But now his restraint too
hath suffered diminution

489
00:45:18,034 --> 00:45:22,562
O Ravana! It's not too
late to beg for mercy!

490
00:45:23,039 --> 00:45:24,631
May the glory of truth be
proclaimed by beat of drum!

491
