are you talking about?

583
00:56:28,871 --> 00:56:31,567
No, no Vinod, I'm lighting a bulb here.

584
00:56:32,708 --> 00:56:34,835
John is beginning to lose it by the day.

585
00:56:35,044 --> 00:56:36,773
Speak to him, and
buy me some more time.

586
00:56:36,946 --> 00:56:39,676
We've started working nights.
- Common Vinod handle it for me.

587
00:56:39,882 --> 00:56:41,179
I'll talk to you later.

588
00:56:41,283 --> 00:56:43,012
Bye.
- Bye.

589
00:56:51,894 --> 00:57:00,427
25 x 75 is equal to...
- 1875.

590
00:57:10,245 --> 00:57:15,046
23.3 x 33.9

591
00:57:20,756 --> 00:57:24,385
789.87 = 790.

592
00:57:52,688 --> 00:57:55,885
I'm about to finish this.

593
00:58:09,138 --> 00:58:10,901
I've fallen in love with you.

594
00:58:22,151 --> 00:58:25,450
What did you say? Come again.

595
00:58:37,666 --> 00:58:41,397
See! Just see!

596
00:58:41,670 --> 00:58:46,334
It's you and me, and long solitude!

597
00:58:46,675 --> 00:58:50,805
See! Just see!

598
00:58:51,013 --> 00:58:56,041
How delicate are these shadows!

